	<title>Examples: Orientation</title>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the orientation of <latex>\RNr[2]</latex> given by the pair of vectors <latex>(\Vect{a},\Vect{b})</latex> with</para>
			<para align="center"><latex>\Vect{a}=(4,1)</latex> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <latex>\Vect{b}=(-2,3)</latex></para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>We form the <latex>(2,2)</latex>-matrix with column vectors <latex>\Vect{a}</latex> and <latex>\Vect{b}</latex> and compute its determinant:</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\det [\Vect{a}\ \ \Vect{b}]</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>
					<![CDATA[
\det
\left[
\begin{array}{rr}
4 & -2 \\
1 & 3
\end{array}
\right]
					]]>
				</right>
				<left></left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>
					12 - (-2)
				</right>
				<left></left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right><![CDATA[ 14 > 0 ]]></right>
			</computation>
			<para>Therefore</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\omega(\Vect{a},\Vect{b})</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>+1</right>
			</computation>
			<para>In other words: the pair of vectors <latex>(\Vect{a},\Vect{b})</latex> represents the positive orientation of <latex>\RNr[2]</latex>.</para>
		</answer>
	</showme>
	
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the orientation of <latex>\RNr[3]</latex> represented by the triple of vectors <latex>(\Vect{a},\Vect{b},\Vect{c})</latex> with</para>
			<para align="center"><latex>\Vect{a} = (1,0,-1)</latex>, <latex>\Vect{b}=(4,-1,2)</latex>, and <latex>\Vect{c}=(3,2,1)</latex>.</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>We form the <latex>(3,3)</latex>-matrix with column vectors <latex>\Vect{a}</latex>, <latex>\Vect{b}</latex>, and <latex>\Vect{c}</latex>; then we compute its determinant:</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\det [\Vect{a}\ \ \Vect{b}\ \ \Vect{c}]</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>
					<![CDATA[
\det
\left[
\begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 4  & 3 \\
0 & -1 & 2 \\
-1 & 2  & 1
\end{array}
\right]
					]]>
				</right>
				<left></left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>
					1\cdot (-1 - 4)\ -\ 1\cdot (8 + 3)
				</right>
				<left></left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right><![CDATA[ -16 < 0 ]]></right>
			</computation>
			<para>Therefore</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\omega(\Vect{a},\Vect{b},\Vect{c})</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>-1</right>
			</computation>
			<para>In other words: the triple of vectors <latex>(\Vect{a},\Vect{b},\Vect{c})</latex> represents the negative orientation of <latex>\RNr[2]</latex>.</para>
		</answer>
	</showme>
